TY  - JOUR
T1  - Diagonalization of Quadratic Forms by Gauss Elimination
AU  - Beightler, Charles S.
AU  - Wilde, Douglass J.
Y1  - 1966/01/01
PY  - 1966
DA  - 1966/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.12.5.371
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.12.5.371
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 371
EP  - 379
VL  - 12
IS  - 5
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The La Grange linear similarity transformation (completing the square) can be used to remove all cross-product terms from a quadratic form. It is shown that the La Grange transformation may be found conveniently by adapting the well-known Gauss elimination procedure for solving linear equations. A simple algorithm for finding the inverse transformation is given. This diagonalization scheme takes much less effort than finding the characteristic roots and vectors. It produces important simplifications in quadratic programming, statistics, and optimization problems.
AB  - The La Grange linear similarity transformation (completing the square) can be used to remove all cross-product terms from a quadratic form. It is shown that the La Grange transformation may be found conveniently by adapting the well-known Gauss elimination procedure for solving linear equations. A simple algorithm for finding the inverse transformation is given. This diagonalization scheme takes much less effort than finding the characteristic roots and vectors. It produces important simplifications in quadratic programming, statistics, and optimization problems.
