N2  - In Eisenberg, E. 1962. Supports of a convex function. Bull. Amer. Math. Soc. 68 192?195, Eisenberg has given a characterization of the set of all supports of a convex function defined on a polyhedral convex cone. This extends the famous Farkas' Lemma and is very useful in programming problems. In this paper we will show that the result is true even for a larger class of convex functions.
